<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,150,464]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,323,223,248]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Stainton, 1849" authorityName="Stainton" authorityYear="1849" box="[592,955,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Eudonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="truncicolella">
<emphasis box="[592,765,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">E. truncicolella</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Stainton" box="[780,948,223,247]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" refString="Stainton, H. T. (1849) An attempt at a Systematic Catalogue of the British Tineidae &amp; Pterophoridae. John van Voorst, i - iv, 1 - 32." type="book chapter" year="1849">
Stainton, 
<number box="[888,948,223,247]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="1849.0">1849</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished by the valva conspicuously concave ventrally at base in the male genitalia; by the ductus bursae holding two posterior loops, and the signum situated at posterior area of the corpus bursae in the femlae genitalia. In 
<taxonomicName box="[1122,1299,296,320]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Eudonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="truncicolella">
<emphasis box="[1122,1299,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">E. truncicolella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the ventral margin of the valva is nearly straight; the ductus bursae has a posterior and an anterior loop, and the signum is placed at middle of the corpus bursae. This species is also similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[960,1123,368,392]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Eudonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lijiangensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[960,1123,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">E. lijiangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1134,1200,368,392]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1134,1200,368,392]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, and the differences between them are stated under 
<taxonomicName box="[498,658,404,428]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Eudonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lijiangensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[498,658,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">E. lijiangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[666,729,404,428]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[666,729,404,428]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
